 as Rainer Maria Rilke, James Joyce, Georges Bataille, and Charlie Chaplin. Poetry in Pieces sheds new light on one of the key figures in twentieth-century Latin American literature, while exploring ways of rethinking the parameters of international lyric modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPeruvian poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  aamerican literature.  aavant garde.  acanon.  acesar vallejo.  aclassic.  ainternational modernism.  ainterwar paris.  ainterwar period.  alatin america.  alatin american poetry.  aliterary criticism.  aliterature.  alyric modernity.  amodernism.  amodernity.  amulticultural.  aparis.  aperu.  aperuvian literature.  apoetry.  apolitics.  asouth america.  awestern canon.  aworld literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026229440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094828040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948280423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520948280/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY